  <description type="morphology">Plants gregarious or in dense mats, hoary white. Stems 0.5–1(–1.5) cm, evenly foliate, weakly julaceous. Leaves erect-spreading when moist, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, somewhat concave, 0.3–1(–1.5) mm; base concolorous; margins recurved proximally, plane distally; apex acute, not cucullate, hyaline in distal 1/2 of leaf; costa long-excurrent, awn slender, hyaline, &lt;recurved when dry&gt;; proximal laminal cells quadrate or short-rectangular, 10–16 µm wide, 1–2:1; distal cells elongate-hexagonal, 40–60 × 10–16 µm, 4–5:1, walls somewhat thickened to distinctly incrassate. Specialized asexual reproduction absent. Seta brown to red-brown, 1–2 cm. Capsule brown to red-brown, ovate, (1–)2–3 mm; hypophysis differentiated, somewhat thickened and rugose. Spores 8–15 µm.</description>
